1 About

Updates on

  • Report 3: Corrected multi-trait omnibus association test on body-related traits in UKBiobank
  • Report 2: Single- and multi-trait association analysis on body-related traits in UKBiobank.

1.1 Additional phenotypes

Additional phenotypes are derived from body_BMIz_orth by down-sampling:

  • body_BMIz_orth_10: 10% of data entries in body_BMIz_orth are left; the rest is set to missing data;
  • body_BMIz_orth_25: 25%
  • body_BMIz_orth_50: 50%

2 Phenotypic correlations

Plots:

  • phenotypic correlations estimated on raw data of phenotypes (100% sample size);
  • phenotypic correlations (\(\rho = \rho_g + \rho_e\)) estimated on summary stats by LDSC;
    • off-diagonal entries from bi-variate LDSC + \(Ns/sqrt(N_1 N_2)\) correction factor;
    • diagonal entries from uni-variate LDSC;
  • absolute (signed) errors;
  • relative (signed) errors.

Height is excluded from the multi-trait analysis.
